    {
        "author_association": "NONE",
        "body": "Previous implementation was great if what you were going for was 100% what Bootstrap was giving to you, but as soon as you've tried to do something else (eg. notifications list in dropdown, custom carousel slide, etc ect.), this approach was quickly making your life miserable, forcing you to write resets for Bootstrap's styles.\r\n\r\nThis also went in other way, when you've tried to reuse styles from other item (eg. put link-like button in dropdown), you've had to dig up Bootstrap's styles and copy them over.\r\n\r\nHence explicit classes we've got now.\r\n",
